This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for assessing the quality of generated images in Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) without interfering with the learning procedure or affecting the learning objective. The paper also presents empirical results on CIFAR-10 to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper deals with image generation and quality assessment. 

Additionally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular topic in AI research. 

The sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as GANs are a type of neural network. 

Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) as the paper deals with image generation and quality assessment, which are important topics in computer graphics.
